# Environment Configuration

This file contains placeholders for required API keys and configuration.
DO NOT commit actual credentials to version control.

## Auth0 Configuration

Create a free Auth0 account at https://auth0.com

Required settings:
- AUTH0_DOMAIN=your-tenant.auth0.com
- AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
- AUTH0_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8080/dashboard.html (or your production URL)

## Firebase Configuration

Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com

Required settings:
- FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key
- FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
- FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
- FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
- FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
- FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

## DocuSign Configuration

Create a DocuSign developer account at https://developers.docusign.com

Required settings:
- DOCUSIGN_INTEGRATOR_KEY=your_integrator_key
- DOCUSIGN_ACCOUNT_ID=your_account_id
- DOCUSIGN_ENVIRONMENT=demo (or production)

Template IDs:
- DOCUSIGN_NDA_TEMPLATE_ID=your_nda_template_id
- DOCUSIGN_LPA_TEMPLATE_ID=your_lpa_template_id

## Plaid Configuration

Create a Plaid account at https://plaid.com

Required settings:
- PLAID_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
- PLAID_SECRET=your_secret
- PLAID_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key
- PLAID_ENV=sandbox (or development/production)

## Security Notes

1. Never commit real API keys to version control
2. Use environment variables or secure secret management in production
3. Rotate credentials regularly
4. Use different credentials for development, staging, and production
5. Enable MFA on all service accounts
6. Monitor API usage and set up alerts for unusual activity
